comment._content: The chap on the rhs is NSW Premier Sir George Fuller adb.anu.edu.au/biography/fuller-sir-george-warburton-6256 ...the chap on the lhs might be Contre-Amiral (Rear-Admiral) Gilly, commander of the French squadron which visited Australia and New Zealand in 1922-1923 ; this Sydney Mail item has another pic of the two but the image quality is poor news.google.com/newspapers?id=rrcoAAAAIBAJ&sjid=KJIDA... ; this is a slightly better pic of Gilly news.google.com/newspapers?id=rrcoAAAAIBAJ&sjid=KJIDA... Pic possibly taken at the reception for officers of the visiting French ships Jules Michelet and Victor Hugo, which was held at Parliament House, Sydney, on 5/1/1923.
